<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Pledges Increased Cooperation With Kuwait City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Jia Qinglin, mayor of the Chinese
capital, pledged here today to increase cooperation and exchanges
between Beijing and Kuwait City.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with a delegation from Kuwait City headed by Mayor
Abdui Rahmanai-Houty, Jia said China and Kuwait have enjoyed good
relations since the two countries established diplomatic
relations, with trade and economic cooperation and exchanges
being on the rise in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that the current visit by the Kuwait City
delegation will further facilitate the cooperation and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Houty said Beijing and Kuwait City are to sign a friendship and
cooperation memorandum, which will raise the cooperation between
the two capitals to a new height.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Jia and Houty signed a memorandum on
cooperation in fields including urban administration,
planning and construction, environmental protection and fire
prevention.
</P>
<P>
The delegation visited Beijing's economic development zone
before the meeting, and is scheduled to visit Shanghai later.
</P>
</TEXT>
