<HEADLINE> Europe's Largest University Campus to be Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A university and Cultural Campus
named "Romania of Tomorrow", estimated to be the largest one in
Europe, will be be built in Bucharest, capital of Romania.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Capital's General Council approved the construction
within the city area, reported the national Rompres news agency on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The campus covering 57,282 square meters will host 20,000
students and comprise 24 faculties and colleges. It will include
amphitheatres, laboratories, on-screen projection halls and a
multipurpose hall with a capacity of 2,500 seats, a 16-storey
three-star hotel with over 1000 beds. Another group of 20-storey
hotels for visiting professors and participants will be set in
place.
</P>
