Countries in resolving conflicts in Africa, Chissano said
that leaders from the Portuguese-speaking African countries held
meeting on the crisis in Guinea Bissau on June 12 when they are
attending the OAU summit in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso, and
informed the regional organization of the situation in that
country.
</P>
<P>
He said that OAU passed a resolution,"condemning
the use of violence in forcing political reform in Guinea
Bissau."
</P>
<P>
Since the crisis erupted in the tiny western African country
in early June, hundreds of people have been killed during
fightings between the government soldiers and the mutineers.
