<HEADLINE> Fifth BITME Exhibition Opens in Bucharest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bucharest, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The fifth BITME international
exhibition of machinery and equipment for the textile industry
started on Tuesday in Bucharest, capital of Romania.
</P>
<P>
"BITME offers this year the latest technologies with respect to
all kinds of machinery for spinning, twisting or winding, weaving
preparatory machinery, weaving and carpet machinery, knitting and
hosiery machinery for the garment industry, as well as other
textile equipment and machinery, testing and measuring equipment,"
said George Cojocaru, General Manager of ROMEXPO, and the main
organizer of the exhibition, at the inauguration of the
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
"All these, through the high amplitude, show a new climate of
performance, competence and intelligence within real competition,
a climate that came true thanks to those who get themselves
involved in the potentials of the Romanian light industry," he
added.
</P>
<P>
"The Romanian textile industry needs fresh infusion of soft
equipments and technologies", Cojocaru said, adding that "The
every year exhibitors' larger number means maybe the best possible
proof that BITME has already become a stable part in the minds of
the specialists and public alike."
</P>
<P>
"Ever since its start, BITME has illustrated, through increased
participation of prestigious foreign companies, a great interest
not only for the Romanian market, but also a challenging
competition of the brand new technologies, an attempt to emulate
all specialists, technologists and merchants," Cojocaru said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibitors are from 19 countries, including Austria,
Belgium, Bulgaria, the Czech Republic, France, Germany, Britain,
Hungary, Italy, the Netherlands, Romania, Spain, Switzerland, and
for the first time this year, Finland, Israel, Japan,
Liechtenstein, the United States and Sweden.  
</P>
