<HEADLINE> Burley Goal Keeps Scotland in Picture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A 67th-minute equalizer from Craig
Burley forced a 1-1 draw for Scotland against Norway here on Tuesday,
saving the team from being the first squad ruled out of the second
stage in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
After a goalless first half, Havard Flo of German side Werder
Bremen put the Scandinavians ahead less than one minute into the
second half.
</P>
<P>
Vidar Riseth, earning his starting place on the expense of striker
Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, dribbled on the left almost to the goalline
before floating the ball to the far post for Flo to head home.
</P>
<P>
Scotland, who lost to defending champions Brazil in the opening
game, retained their composure and then rallied strongly.
</P>
<P>
After receiving a central long pass from behind, Burley calmly
lobbed the ball into net over goalkeeper Forde Grodas.
</P>
<P>
A loss for Scotland would mean they had no chance to enter the
16-team second stage.
</P>
<P>
Gordon Durie and Darren Jackson were the Scots who were cautioned
with yellow cards by Hungarian coach Laszio Vagner while Norway's
Kjetil Rekdal and Henning Berg were also warned. 
</P>
