that there have many goals in this first round of compeition, in the
first 16 matches, an average of 2.3 goals were scored in each
match-up." said Platini.
</P>
<P>
Platini said some of the small teams overestimated their
opponents. "They focused too much on defence, with the unique
objective of ending up in a draw," Platini said, "It's unfortunate,
because these teams definitely have the means to surprise us.
Nonetheless, I expect they will step their performance up a notch in
the coming matches."
</P>
<P>
As a former soccer star himself, Platini said not a single player
has impressed him greatly. "As far as I am concerned, a great player
is one who makes the right pass at the right time." 
</P>
