<HEADLINE> 10 Tonnes of Drugs Seized in Istanbul Since 1991 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- About 10 tonnes of drugs was seized
in Turkey's largest city of Istanbul in police operations since
January 1991, the Anatolia News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,713 anti-narcotics operations has been conducted
by police in Istanbul, which links Asia and Europe, during the
period.
</P>
<P>
Istanbul police figures showed that 6,418.3 kilograms of
heroin, 3,132.3 kilograms of hashish, 81.2 kilograms of cocaine as
well as 225 kilograms of opium were seized in the operations.
</P>
<P>
The most concentrated actions were taken in 1993 with the
seizure of 1,121.5 kilograms of heroin and 1,684.6 kilograms of
hashish.
</P>
<P>
Istanbul has grown into a center of drugs trade in Turkey,
police officials said.
</P>
<P>
International drug dealers often use Turkey as a channel
trafficking narcotics from Asian production countries to the
European markets. 
</P>
