<HEADLINE> Scotland Coach Says Should Have Won </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Scotland coach Craig Brown said his
team should have won Tuesday's game against Norway in group A of the
World Cup finals here.
</P>
<P>
"The only time we were out of the game was a 10-minute spell after
their goal. I thought we controlled the remainder of the match," Brown
said.
</P>
