"We always have a habit of coming back - I would love to think that
sometime soon we'll get ahead in the game and then I think we can go
on from strength to strength," he added.
</P>
<P>
Brown said he was very disappointed with one point because he
thought the team had done enough to get all three points.
</P>
<P>
The coach said, "We're still here and we'll be fighting to the
end."
</P>
<P>
He was pleased with the decision to put Craig Burley ahead into
midfield from defence in the 1-1 draw.
</P>
<P>
Burley's equalizer in the 67th minute kept their hope to reach the
second stage alive.
</P>
<P>
Burley said after the game, "When the Norwegians scored, we were a
little demoralized but we continued to play well."
</P>
<P>
He added, "I took advantage of an opening in the defence and I saw
that a Norwegian defender was out of position and the goalie had come
out, so I lobbed it in to equlize."
</P>
<P>
Burley said, "Today we were a better team, we could have won it
several times, but we did not quite make it. If we manage to beat
Morocco (on June 23), we still have a chance to qualify."
</P>
<P>
Norway coach Egil Olsen was disappointed at the result, saying "I
thought we could have done better. We are still in the tournament."
</P>
<P>
He added, "We were in control (in the second half) until Scotland
equalized. After that we lost it." 
