<HEADLINE> Direct Trade Improving Sino-Russian Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A direct trade "Corridor", or
commodities distribution center, for China and Russia officially
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
It will provide Chinese manufacturers with a special channel
for selling their products directly to Russia and other members of
the Commonwealth of Independent States, according to center
officials.
</P>
<P>
The "Corridor" starts at a port by Suifenhe city in northeast
China, where there is a storage, wholesale base, and an exhibition
center, and ends in the city of Altem in Russia, where there is a
bonded zone and a wholesale market.
</P>
<P>
About ten types of goods will be handled in the corridor, like
household electric appliances, building materials, hardware,
furniture, food, and clothing. 
