<DOCNO> XIE19980617.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Thirds of Ethiopia's Land Prone to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Environmental Protection
Authority of Ethiopia said Wednesday that 70 percent of
Ethiopia's land is exposed to desertification.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here to mark the World Desertification
Day which has been observed on June 17 since 1994, the authority
said the size of forest area in Ethiopia which protects leaching
has been reduced to only three percent.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government is taking measures to sustainably
address the problem of desertification, the authority said,
adding, the Ethiopian parliament has endorsed the international
convention on the prevention of desertification and issued
directives for its implementation.
</P>
<P>
The preparation of the national desertification prevention
program is underway to implement the international convention,
the authority added.
</P>
<P>
The World Desertification Day was established following the
agreement on the United Nations convention to combat
desertification in 1994.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics available, about 900 million people
across the world suffer from desertification-related problems, of
whom 80 percent live in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
In Africa, one-third of the population suffers from this
problem, while three-fourths of the people of the member
countries of the Inter-Governmental Authority on Development
(IGAD) are facing the problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
