country's soccer association would issue a official press release to
announce the date of his departure.
</P>
<P>
Gomez said, "He may be young but the rules still apply to him.
Moreover, the comments he made aren't justified as there were no
tactical problems against Romania."
</P>
<P>
The expulsion came as a surprise for most of the Colombian players
but Carlos Valderrama said the team was still united.
</P>
<P>
Asprilla had told the Colombian radio reporter that he thought he
had not played badly and teammates had played worse without being
taken off, apparently referring to playmaker Valderrama. 
