<HEADLINE> Kiriyenko: Russia to Carry out Anticrisis Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko on Wednesday called on the government to show courage
and political will in implementing its economic anti-crisis
program, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
At the opening session of the second economic forum of the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) in St. Petersburg,
Kiriyenko said the program would be unpopular in certain areas,
but the government would have to carry it out.
</P>
<P>
He said the country's financial and economic crisis was due to
both external and internal causes, but mainly the latter.
</P>
<P>
The main cause, in his view, was the crisis of confidence in a
system which lived beyond its means, funding expenditure with
external and internal borrowings.
</P>
<P>
The government's priority was to establish a tight budget
policy and support industrial production, Kiriyenko said. Only
"firm budget stabilization" could help overcome the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The anticrisis program will be presented to the enlarged
government meeting on June 23, in front of President Boris Yeltsin
and members of parliament, he announced.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,000 delegates from the CIS states are taking part in the
St. Petersburg forum, the largest economic congress of the CIS.
</P>
</TEXT>
