<HEADLINE> Buddhist Festival Scheduled For Chinese Sacred Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) --A major Buddhist ritual prayer for
world peace and auspiciousness will be held from August 9 to 11 at
Mount Wutai, a sacred Buddhist mountain in north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The festival is being sponsored by Daxiantong Temple there and
Beijing's Xintaiyang Film and Television Cultural Development
Corp. It is a major part of the Ninth Mount Wutai International
Tourist Month, celebrating Buddhist culture with a series of
Buddhist rites and cultural performances.
</P>
<P>
Mount Wutai, one of the four sacred Buddhist mountains in
China, has 47 temples, the earliest of which dates back to the
Tang Dynasty(618-907)
</P>
<P>
The mountain had 600,000 tourists last year, and made about 145
million yuan (about 18 million US dollars) from tourism, an
increase of 20 percent from the previous year. 
