<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Self-Discipline In China's Securities Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China's major securities firms
today called for increased awareness of the law, risks, and
service to get the securities market to contribute more to
economic development.
</P>
<P>
This comes from more than 300 representatives from across China
who participated in a two-day meeting sponsored by the Securities
Association of China.
</P>
<P>
They said that the laws and regulations of China's securities
market are not perfect and the quality of professionals falls
short of what is needed. Securities firms need to deal with
unethical behavior, they said.
</P>
<P>
China's securities market began when the stock exchanges in
Shanghai and Shenzhen were founded in the early 1990s. China now
has 327 major securities firms, and 2,440 securities offices.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 800 Chinese companies that are listed and
about 34 million investors.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that as China increases its market economy
reforms, the securities market becomes more important and provides
a very important venue for the cash-starved state-owned
enterprises to raise funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
