<HEADLINE> 3 Israeli Settlers Arrested for Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Israeli police arrested three
Jewish settlers on Wednesday, who were suspected of killing a
Palestinian farmer in the West Bank, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the settlers, two of them minors, beat
the Palestinian farmer to death with a wooden bat on Tuesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when the farmer, Abdel Majid Turki, met
the suspected assailants along a main road near the Jewish
settlement of Beit Hagai, south of the West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
One of the suspects said that they beat Turki just for
"playing a prank." And police have not given a motive.
</P>
<P>
Turki was sent to a hospital in Hebron, where his skull was
found fractured and later he died. His body was taken to Tel Aviv
for an autopsy.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, a Jerusalem magistrate also called the three
settlers for a hearing to extend their detention.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place in the sensitive Hebron area, where the
Jewish settlers have involved in frequent clashes with the
Palestinian residents in recent years. And in 1994, a Jewish
settler shot and killed 29 Muslim worshippers in a Hebron
mosque. 
</P>
