<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Launches HK Dollar Debt Issuance Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Mortgage
Corporation (HKMC) Wednesday launched a Debt Issuance Program,
which involves 20 billion HK dollars (2.56 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The corporation signed an agreement here Wednesday with five
primary dealers and 12 selling group members appointed for the
program, which is aimed at further enhancing the HKMC's ability to
raise funds through the debt market.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Financial Secretary Donald Tsang, who
is also chairman of the HKMC, said: "The launching of the Debt
Issuance Program is a timely development crucial to the successful
operation of the HKMC."
</P>
<P>
Under the innovative program, five primary dealers who have
good access to institutional investors are appointed to play the
role of underwriter and market maker for securities issued while
12 selling group members are appointed to help with the
distribution of the debt securities.
</P>
<P>
The program will complement a 20-billion-HK dollar Note
Issuance Program introduced by the HKMC in January 1998. The
previous program takes financial institutions as its main client
base while the new one targets institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The two programs together provide a comprehensive coverage of
the investor base of the Hong Kong dollar debt market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
