<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CITIC Global Tourism Network Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Beginning today, travelers in
China can order hotels and other tourist service programs in more
than 70 countries through CITIC-SPY Internet Global Tourism Order
Network.
</P>
<P>
SPY Internet Global Tourism Ordering Network, which was opened
by Singapore Linbert Travel under the support of the Singaporean
government, provides order services for more than 5,000 star-rated
hotels in the world, including more than 500 in China, as well as
such tourist services as plane, train and boat tickets,
sightseeing, and car rentals.
</P>
<P>
The China International Trust and Investment Corporation
(CITIC) became the sole agent of the SPY tourist network by
signing a cooperative agreement with Linbert in March of this
year, said Yao Jinrong, vice-president of CITIC, at today's news
conference.
</P>
<P>
The CITIC-SPY network will join the ticket-booking network of
the Civil Aviation Administration of China and the Ministry of
Railways to spread its use in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The number of global users of the Internet has increased
sharply in recent years. In China, the figure reached 1.06 million
by May 30 of this year, according to statistics from the Chinese
Academy of Sciences. Experts believe that the opening of the
CITIC-SPY network will offer more convenience for travelers in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
