<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Wednesday on technical
support.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index ended 15.04
points higher at 450.88 and the all-share Emas Index added 3.04
points to 116.86 while the Industrial Index rose nine points to
887 and the Second Board index 0.7 of a point to 103.55.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 424 to 159 with 170 counters
unchanged while 188 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover, however, dipped slightly to 132.368 million
shares valued at 290.435 million ringgit (71.712 million U.S.
dollars) from Tuesday's 133.820 million shares worth 292.628
million ringgit (72.253 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
