<HEADLINE> 11 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Tuesday killed 11 Tamil rebels in the Northern Province of the
country, according to a military spokesman Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops confronted a group of Tamil
rebels and engaged them with small arms east of Mankulam town
Tuesday morning. The troops confirmed that three rebels were
killed in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday evening, government troops killed six Tamil rebels
in an ambush southeast of Mankulam town, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said in another incident around 7:15 a.m. Tuesday,
government troops killed two rebels northeast of Ampakaman.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, attack aircraft of the Sri Lankan air force engaged
targets northeast of Mankulam town Tuesday, said the spokesman,
adding that according to monitored rebel transmission the rebels
suffered heavy casualties in the air attack.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of
the country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
