<HEADLINE> Rainstorm, Hailstones Batter Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A rainstorm and hailstones struck
China's northern port city of Tianjin for 12 consecutive hours
between 5 p.m. Tuesday and 5 a.m. today. The storm flattened to
varying degrees standing crops in the fields and hindered urban
traffic.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the local meteorological department said that the
rainfall, sweeping extensively over the whole municipality,
averaged 71.5 millimeters (mm) in the urban areas, with Dongli
District receiving as much as 125.3 mm.
</P>
<P>
Egg-like hailstones dropped in a number of districts and
outskirtan counties, and brought damages to apples, grapes,
vegetables and grain.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, because of prompt weather forecast prior to the
rain and hails, the relevant local departments took preventive
measures to stop the hail by launching more than 1,000 artillery
shells.  
</P>
</TEXT>
