<HEADLINE> Nigeria Bans Import of 16 Chemicals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has banned the importation
of 16 chemicals considered to be harmful to the environment,
media reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The list issued by the Federal Environmental Protection Agency
include heptachlor, fluoroacetamide, mercury compounds,
chlordane, chlordimeform, asbestos/crocidolite, DDT, aldrin and
dieldrin.
</P>
<P>
Others are dinoseb and dinoseb salts, pentachlorophenol,
chlorobezilate, EDB and mixed isomers.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made according to a recommendation of a
special committee with officials from the Ministry of
Agriculture, the National Agency for Food and Drug Administration
Control, the Institute of Chartered Chemists and others, the
reports said. 
</P>
