<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen people were killed and 33
injured in a bus-train crash this morning in Huaihua, a city in
central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
A bus with 50 passengers ran into a cargo train at the
crossing between Tonghui County and the city of Hongjiang
around 1:50 a.m. (Beijing time). The bus was pushed some 30 meters
after the collision.
</P>
<P>
