<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Build First Environmental Protection Industry Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, plans to build China's first
environmental protection industry park.
</P>
<P>
A city government official said the park will include three
parts -- a zone for development and production of environmental
protection technology and devices, a zone for disposal and
recycling of industrial wastes, and an environmental and ecological
demonstration zone.
</P>
<P>
Located in three places in the city, the park is expected to be
built within two years.
</P>
<P>
The official said the park will be engaged in the development
and production of new technology and devices for environmental
protection, as well as non-pollution vegetables and high-tech
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The disposal of toxic industrial wastes will also be a major
function of the part.
</P>
<P>
He said the park will introduce environmental protection
technology from Hong Kong for some projects. 
</P>
