<HEADLINE> Air China, U.S. Airline Sign Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Air China and Northwest Airlines
of the United States will forge closer ties in sales promotions,
according to an agreement signed recently.
</P>
<P>
The two airlines will coordinate their flight plans and
connections, and their computer booking systems will be
linked. Northwest Airlines will provide Air China with some seats
on Sino-U.S. flights and U.S. domestic flights. On flights managed
by Air China across the Pacific Ocean, Northwest Airlines is
entiled to sell some tickets.
</P>
<P>
