<HEADLINE> China, ROK Agree on Plan for Chinese Tourism to Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China and the Republic of Korea
(ROK) have agreed on measures to open ROK as a tourist
destination for Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum signed by the country's tourism, foreign affairs
and public security departments shows:
</P>
<P>
-- China will select some provinces and municipalities as test
sites to carry out the business. When sound trust is established
between travel agencies of the two countries, more Chinese travel
agencies will be allowed to conduct the business;
</P>
<P>
-- Both sides will choose a group of travel agencies with
sufficient assets and service capability to handle the business;
and
</P>
<P>
-- Tourists will be allowed to visit ROK only in the form of
tour groups of nine or above.
</P>
<P>
Some influential newspapers of ROK recently praised the effort
of the Chinese government as "a huge support for ROK to overcome
its financial crisis."
</P>
<P>
Tourism, a pillar industry of ROK, earns the country billions
of U.S. dollars in foreign currency every year.
</P>
<P>
ROK expects to host 500,000 to one million Chinese tourists
annually in the future, earning 500 million to one billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
ROK is the seventh tourist destination approved by the Chinese
government for Chinese citizens at their own expense following
Singapore, Malaysia, the Philippines, Thailand, Australia and New
Zealand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
