<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Project Hope Helps 33,000 Dropouts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Pang Pingping, a 13-year-old girl
in east China's Anhui Province, went back to school after several
months as a dropout with the help of a grandmother she didn't know
in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Pang was only one of more than 30,000 beneficiaries of
Shanghai's Project Hope to help poor children return to school.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that Project Hope in this leading
economic powerhouse has helped 33,000 dropouts in other parts of
China return to school.
</P>
<P>
In the past four years, the office in charge of the project
received 76 million yuan in contributions, setting up nearly 500
"hope" schools across the country to provide learning
opportunities for 33,000 dropouts.
</P>
<P>
So far, the municipality has held more than 40 large-scale
fund-raisers such as auctions and sports competitions with the
proceeds going to the project. 
</P>
