<DOCNO> XIE19980617.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Capital of 12 Dynasties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Xi'an, capital of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province, has been political center for 12 dynasties
lasting more than 1,100 years. Now, It is still the economic and
cultural center of northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Located in the center of the rich and fertile Central Shaanxi
Plain, the city has been a strategic military spot in history.
</P>
<P>
Because of its superior natural resources, Xi'an is where the
earliest stone-age humans were found to have existed -- the
Lantian apeman of one million years ago. The Ruins of the Banpo
Culture displays the matriarchal society of 6,000 to 7,000 years
ago. And, the Keshengzhuang Ruins, dating back 4,000 years,
indicates that ancient man had evolved to a patriarchal society by
then.
</P>
<P>
In 221 B.C., Qin Shi Huang united China and set up the Qin
Dynasty, the first feudal dynasty in the Chinese history. He named
himself "the First Emperor," and he built his capital in Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
In the ensuing Han Dynasty (206 B.C.-220 A.D.), Xi'an was the
only city in the world that could stand side-by-side with Rome.
</P>
<P>
During the Tang Dynasty (618-907), Xi'an became
the single biggest international metropolis in the world with a
population of one million.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an was the starting point of the Silk Road, a route throught
which China's silk, tea, compasses, as well as the expertise to
make paper, gunpowder and herbal medicines were exported to West
Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Today's Xi'an, home to the world famous terra cotta warriors
and horses, is also the biggest modern industrial and commercial
center of northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an's trade ties have been extended to more than 100
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
It is also linked to more than 50 cities in China by direct air
flights, and non-stop air routes to Japan and some other countries
have also been opened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980617.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
