<HEADLINE> Annan Visits Museums in Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 16 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General Kofi
Annan Tuesday visited two museums in Rome as an ordinary tourist.
</P>
<P>
Annan and his wife, Nane, were shown the restored equestrian
statue of Marcus Aurelius and taken through the two museums on the
Capitoline Hill. The two museums, facing each other across a
square, were designed by Michelangelo.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Annan were Italian ambassador to the United
Nations Francesco Paolo Fulei and Rome mayor Francesco Rutelli.
</P>
<P>
Annan arrived here Monday to open a five-week conference on
setting up an International Criminal Court for crimes against
humanity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
