<HEADLINE> Plant Diseases, Insect Pests Threaten Forests in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The government has allocated 1
million yuan (120,481 U.S. dollars) to save extensive areas of
trees threatened by plant diseases and insect pests in northwest
China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
To date, the total area of trees threatened by plant diseases
and insect pests has reached 133,333 hectares, today's China Youth
Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The disaster was attributed to abnormal climatic conditions and
began 20 days earlier than in previous years. Experts said the
long growing period of trees in the province also increased the
chance of plant diseases and insect pests.
</P>
<P>
The disaster was first discovered in Minhe Autonomous County of
Hui and Tu nationalities in the eastern part of the province on
May 27.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province felled nearly 100,000 trees suffering
inroads caused by insect pests in order to prevent the spread of
the disaster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
