<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Suffering Serious Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Floods have inundated most of
east China's Jiangxi Province, but no casualties have been
reported.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rains since June 12 have affected 210,000 people in
four cities and 25 counties in the province. No harvest will be
reaped on 33,000 hectares of land because of the floods.
</P>
<P>
More torrential rain and hailstorms are expected to hit the
northern and central parts of the province, according to the
weather forecasters.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has issued a circular urging
localities in stricken areas to fight against floods. Those
suffering no flood damage so far have been alerted to possible
hazards. 
</P>
