<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sihanouk Calls On Cambodians to Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk
Wednesday called on Cambodians to take an active part in the
upcoming general elections.
</P>
<P>
The king said in the message that the elections scheduled for
July 26 would be "free and democratic," and conducted in a secret
way.
</P>
<P>
He asked the people not to be afraid of anyone or any political
party. They should feel free to exercise their right to vote and
select their favorite political candidate at will, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 75-year-old monarch returned to the northern town of Siem
Reap on April 11 from Beijing, China after three months' medical
treatment. His stay at home is expected to benefit the forthcoming
elections and the stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
So far, 97.24 percent of the 5.5 million voters have registered
during the four-week registration to vote for the 122 members of
parliament. More than 11,3000 polling stations will be set up in
23 electoral districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
