<HEADLINE> Japanese Urge India, Pakistan to Stop Developing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A visiting three-member
Japanese anti-nuclear team has appealed to the people of India and
Pakistan to stop developing nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
"We have to strengthen the anti-nuclear movement around the
world, we are here to show our solidarity with peace groups in
South Asia," said Ken Sakamoto, secretary general of Gensuikin
(Japanese Congress Against A and H Bombs) and one of the
three-member team presently in Indian capital New Delhi Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
People in Japan had been shocked to hear about the nuclear
tests conducted by India and so the team, which includes a
Hiroshima survivor, has come over to India to talk to the people
here and show solidarity with those opposing the nuclear test, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese delegation, which has come equipped with several
photographs and two video films depicting the destruction at
Hiroshima, plans to travel in north India and spread awareness
about the destructive power of nuclear weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
