<DOCNO> XIE19980617.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Getting Worse in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless people in
Thailand has reached 2.7 million as a result of the deepening
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
The unemployed consist of two groups -- 1.5 million real
unemployed who are ready to work and 1.2 million seasonally
inactive labor force from the agricultural sector, according to a
government press release Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The figure was provided by the Thai National Statistical Office
which conducted a nationwide survey earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Of the total population of 60.9 million in Thailand, 32.1
million are within the work force with 29.4 million employed.
</P>
<P>
New graduate students and other sources of new labor force,
totally estimated at 489,000, will be released to the labor market
within this year, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
If the present economic woes were not addressed, the number of
unemployed would rocket to a "dangerous level", economic experts
warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
