<DOCNO> XIE19980617.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 300-Million-Dollar Loan to Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved a 300
million U.S. dollar loan on Tuesday to help Mexican private
enterprises and institutions of higher learning support economic
and social development.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to encourage excellence in science and
technological research, to increase the availability of scientific
and technological human capital, and to institute development in
strategic fields of importance to the country's social and
economic survival.
</P>
<P>
The project is also designed to support increased productivity
among firms by providing decentralized, demand-driven
technological services for small-and-medium-sized enterprises, and
through the creation of a pilot venture-capital scheme led by the
private sector.
</P>
<P>
The project will also facilitate links between private firms,
universities, and research institutions by providing financial
support for activities and technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is about 662.8 million dollars.
Apart from the World Bank loan, the government of Mexico will
contribute about 209.3 million dollars to the project, with the
Mexican private sector providing some 153.5 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
