<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Education Project in Bolivia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday approved
an interest-free credit equivalent to 75 million U.S. dollars for
an education quality and equity strengthening project in Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Reinforcing the World Bank's commitment to education made at
the Second Summit of the Americas in April this year, the project
aims to increase the number of completed years at school by
students in Bolivia. As recently as 1995 only 20 percent of the
population there completed 12 years of school.
</P>
<P>
The project will help improve the quality of Bolivian education
by financing more than 1400 Municipal Educational Development
Programs. These programs were developed from school improvement
proposals prepared by the parents, teachers and directors from a
nucleus of nine schools reviewed and selected by municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association, the World Bank's concessional lending wing for
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
