<HEADLINE> Argentine Aircraft Lands in Malvinas Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A private airplane with a
U.S. license piloted by an Argentine citizen landed in the
Malvinas (Falkland) Islands, which is now under the control of
Britain.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine Foreign Ministry said Tuesday that the pilot of
the plane, Ernesto Lucio Barcella, had no choice but to land at a
British military base without declaring the cause.
</P>
<P>
The British Embassy described the action as an illegal
immigration, while the Argentine Foreign Ministry announced that
the return of the pilot is being negotiated.
</P>
<P>
A war erupted between Argentina and Britain in 1982 for the
sovereignty over the islands. The Islands, located in the
southern Atlantic Ocean, has been occupied by Britain since
January 3, 1833. 
</P>
