<HEADLINE> U.S. Boxing Team for Goodwill Games Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The 24-man U.S. boxing team for
the Goodwill Games next month in New York was announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Light middleweight Darnell Wilson and heavyweight DaVarryl
Williamson, alternates on the 1996 U.S. Olympic boxing team, will
lead the squad. The boxers were chosen following the U.S.
Challenge this year.
</P>
<P>
"We expect to have success," said Joe Zanders, one of four
coaches for the team. "We expect some people to win gold."
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Wilson is the oldest member of the team. He has
won two straight U.S. championships and took a title from the
U.S. Challenge.
</P>
<P>
Williamson, 29, is the first heavyweight boxer to win three
national titles in a row.
</P>
<P>
Two other medal hopefuls are Larry Mosley in welterweight and
Ricardo Williams in light welterweight. They won the U.S. titles
early this year.
</P>
<P>
The Goodwill Games will be held in New York from July 19 to
August 2. 
</P>
