<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. World Cup Game Attacts Big TV Audience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Americans' opening game
against Germany in the current World Cup Finals Monday drew the
biggest U.S. television audience since the tournament began, but
the rate was still lower than the ABC soap opera it pre-empted.
</P>
<P>
The 40-market overnight rating for the U.S.-Germany battle on
Monday was 4.4, the network said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In 1994 when the World Cup was hosted by the United States, the
three ABC games featuring the Americans averaged a 7.0 rating. ABC
averaged a 5.3 rating overall during the tournament.
</P>
<P>
By comparison, the Belgium-Netherlands game on Saturday had a
2.3 rating and the game Sunday between Jamaica and Croatia had a
2.7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
