<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Marcelo Rios of Chile was
beaten by Italian Gianluca Pozzi in the Nottingham Open tennis
tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rios won the first set 6-3 but conceded the next two sets 6-4,
6-0 to the Italian in a major blow to his chances at Wimbledon,
where he is seeded second behind American Pete Sampras.
</P>
<P>
