<HEADLINE> NBA Players Dropped from US World Championship Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- USA Basketball announced on
Tuesday at the 12 NBA players chosen to represent the United
States will not compete in the World Basketball Championship
starting on July 29 in Athens, Greece.
</P>
<P>
"We are extremely disappointed and regret that this action had
to be taken but training camp for our team starts on July 8 and we
simply cannot wait until July 2 for a decision before we begin the
process of fielding a replacement team," said USA Basketball
executive director Warren Brown.
</P>
<P>
The current NBA labor agreement expires on July 1, and
indications are that a lockout by the owners could be possible.
</P>
<P>
The 12 NBA players chosen to represent the United States spoke
by conference call on June 11 and decided they would not commit to
playing as long as a lockout seemed likely.
</P>
<P>
The dealine for submitting 24-man rosters to FIBA is Friday.
The new team may be made up of the 12-man Goodwill Games team,
college players, or a roster of CBA players and American playing
overseas. The final roster will be made no early than 72 hours
before the tournament starts.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the world championship are teams from Argentina,
Australia, Brazil, Canada, Greece, Italy, Japan, Lithuania,
Nigeria, Puerto Rico, Russia, Senegal, South Korea, Spain and
Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
