<HEADLINE> Croatia's Mine Clearance Will Take 15 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Croatia aims to clear all mines
which were left over by the war and are scattered across 6,000
square kilometers, one ninth of its territory.
</P>
<P>
At the speed of 400 square kilometers a year, with a yearly
labor force of 1000, the task could be fulfilled in 15 years, said
an official in charge of the national mine clearance center.
</P>
<P>
The clearance project, plus the rebuilding of factories,
houses, roads, energy facilities and other war-destroyed
infrastructures would cost 2.5 billion U.S. dollars which, the
official, said would be shared by the state budget and
international loans. 
</P>
