<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists China's Guangxi Urban Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday financing of a total of 92 million U.S. dollars equivalent
for the Guangxi urban environment project in China.
</P>
<P>
The financing comprises a 20 million dollar interest-free
credit and a 72 million dollar loan.
</P>
<P>
This project will help improve the environment of Nanning and
Guilin cities in support of sustainable economic growth and
poverty alleviation in the region.
</P>
<P>
Specifically, the project is aimed to improve the quality of
major water bodies, regulate the flow of the Lijiang river,
improve institutional and financial capacity for environmental
protection, environmental services and water resource management.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the project will implement pilot schemes for control
of sugar refinery pollution.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association, the World Bank's concessional lending wing for
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
