<HEADLINE> Brazil Qualify with 3-0 Win over Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NANTES, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazil became the first team to
qualify for the knock-out stage after beating Morocco 3-0 in a Group
A match on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo ended his four-match goal drought as he opened the
scoring at the 8th minute. The Morocco team made a tactic mistake
by strengthening their attack and that gave the Brazilians more
scoring chances.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo made it 2-0 for Brazil just before the interval and
Bebeto sealed the 3-0 victory at the 50th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team enjoyed such great advantages in the match
they could have scored more goals, but they preferred to
domonstrate their skills instead.
</P>
<P>
Though Morocco lost the match, they still have the chance to
qualify for the top 16 if they can beat Scotland in their last group
match.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, the highspirited Scottish team forced Norway
to a 1-1 draw to keep their hopes alive.
</P>
<P>
Norway and Scotland both have the chance of qualifying as Norway
have garnered two points from as many matches while Scotland and
Morocco each with one point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
