<HEADLINE> CA Joins Hands With Paging Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International, Inc., the leading software maker in the U.S., and
PageNet, a major paging service provider here, announced Tuesday a
joint development and marketing of a powerful paging system.
</P>
<P>
The system will combine PageNet's wireless information delivery
copabilities and CA's flagship product -- Unicenter TNG enterprise
management system -- to produce a highly efficient user friendly
new pager.
</P>
<P>
The new pager, whose hardware is a product of Motorola, looks
like a folded hand-held PC with a keyboard and a little screen.
Its highlights include the two-way massage transmission; sending
and receiving Internet e-mail; faxing data; receiving voice mail;
and PC connectivity.
</P>
<P>
Another function of the pager is that it will allow clients to
receive immediate wireless notification of changes in the working
conditions of their operations. It gives users the ability to
receive wireless alerts and take pre-defined corrective action
regardless of their personal location.
</P>
<P>
Other features of the device include a storage of the user's
messages for up to 72 hours if the device is out of coverage range
or if it is accidentally turned off. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
